<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="critical-adj">critical <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'krɪtɪkl/    美 /'krɪtɪkl/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>批判的；挑剔的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Students are encouraged to develop critical thinking instead of accepting everything they are told without questioning it.
鼓励学生们养成批判性思维而不是毫无置疑地接受被告诉的一切。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>紧要的；关键的</strong></h4>
<p>extremely important：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The first 24 hours after the operation are the most critical.
术后24小时是最关键的。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>These talks are <strong>critical to</strong> the future of the peace process.
这些谈判对和平进程的前景至关重要。</p></div></div>